<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04909</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING THE DISPOSAL OF ELECTRONIC DEVICES AT SOLID WASTE MANAGEMENT FACILITIES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to address improper disposal of electronic devices which poses a great deal of hazard to
humans and the environment as such devices contain a surplus of toxic chemicals like lead, cadmium, 
and mercury, to name a few.

Refers "Electronic Device" to a desktop or laptop computer, computer monitor, portable computer,
cathode ray tube, flat panel television, or cellular phones.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECOLOGY ON 2019-10-02</td></tr></table>